                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 155</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On February 2, President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> directed
                    that the results of the recently-concluded talks with Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> “be reported by the Department of State
                    for the information of the National Security Council.” As a result of this
                    directive, <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName> forwarded a memorandum
                    to <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Executive Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJSJ1">Lay</persName> on February 23 entitled “Results of the
                    Conversations Between the President and the French Prime Minister.” <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJSJ1">Lay</persName> circulated this memorandum immediately to
                    the members of the National Security Council, the Secretary of the Treasury, and
                    the Director of Defense Mobilization as <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 105.
                    Documentation concerning <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 105 is in <gloss
                        target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> files, lot
                    63D351, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 105 Memoranda.</p>
            </div>
